cars.heading: Nissan 300 ZX Twin Turbo 3.0 V6 Manuell, 283hk
cars.description:
Nissan 300ZX Twin Turbo 3.0 V6 Manuell -1991, With a fuel consumption of 11.1 litres/100km - 25 mpg UK - 21 mpg US (Average), 0 to 100 km/h (62mph) in 5.9 seconds, a maximum top speed of 155 mph (250 km/h), a curb weight of 3571 lbs (1620 kgs), the 300 ZX Z32 Twin Turbo has a turbocharged V 6 cylinder engine, with the engine code VG30DETT.

This engine produces a maximum power of 283 PS (279 bhp - 208 kW) at 6400 rpm and a maximum torque of 375 Nm (276 lb.ft) at 3600 rpm. The power is transmitted to the road by the rear wheel drive (RWD) with a 5 speed Manual gearbox.

On the topic of chassis details responsible for road holding, the 300 ZX Z32 has Independent. Double Wishbones. coil springs. anti-roll bar front suspension and Multilink. Coil springs. anti-roll bar rear suspension. Stock tire sizes are 255 / 50 on 16 inch rims at the front, and 255 / 50 on 16 inch rims at the rear. For stopping power, the 300 ZX Z32 Twin Turbo braking system includes Vented Discs at the front and Vented Discs at the rear.

The 300 ZX Z32 model is a car manufactured by Nissan, and available after that as a used car.
